Brazil Says Buying Portugal Debt Is Possibility, Diario Reports

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-03-30T07:35:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/brazil-says-buying-portugal-debt-is-possibility-diario-reports.html
Brazil is studying the best way of
taking part in the process of Portugal’s economic recovery and
one of the possibilities is the purchase of Portuguese sovereign
debt, Diario Economico reported, citing a written interview with
President Dilma Rousseff.  Brazil is also looking at other alternatives such as buying
back Brazilian securities held by the Portuguese government,
Rousseff said, according to the Portuguese newspaper.  It is “premature” to rule out opportunities of
association between oil companies  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  and
 Galp Energia SGPS SA (GALP) , Rousseff was cited as saying in the
newspaper.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
